full_title: HOT TO GO! by Chappell Roan
title: HOT TO GO!

description.plain:
HOT TO GO! is one of many upbeat dance-pop songs on Chappell Roan’s debut album, ‘The Rise and Fall of a Midwest Princess’. For HOT TO GO!, Roan said she wanted a song that she could dance to with her fans, so its cheerleading-style beat, which she also calls a “fantasy” of her high school days, is intentionally crafted to be danced to – Roan teaches her fans the accompanying dance in concerts, with many, including the singer herself, comparing it stylistically to the Village People’s ‘YMCA’.

The intense energy and queerness of the song and music video – colourfully kitschy and raunchy – has earned it the description of “camp” or “campy” by critics and fans.
